<br>
1) Pet haste cap fix of course.<br>
<br>
2) Elemental forms should be 24/7 and zone and also have same fac adjustments as enchanter illusion and not just KOS everywhere.<br>
<br>
3) Other AA skills need to be removed and / or totally reworked. MGB is useless for a mage.<br>
<br>
An Example: First Aid does nothing for a magician seeing as while you can now bind to 80% you can only do 25 hp at a time.  We heal faster with phantom armor and sitting then binding AND we regen mana that way too.  So you could up the cap of bind wounds for magicians to 200 and let us heal a decent amount with bandages as a suggestion.  We are the only caster that uses bandages regularly anyway.<br>
<br>
4) Add a sparse smattering of cold based nukes and rains. One at level 24 or 30 where you sometimes are in places like sol a and forced to use a level16 nuke because all else are fire based and do no damage.<br>
<br>
5) Change the whole shock line to be conjuration based and leave bolts as evocation.<br>
<br>
6) Lower the resist to Malo line. I can rarely land this spell and have since stopped casting it for the most part. Waste of my mana bar to try to get it to stick even after tash.<br>
<br>
7) Instead of voice graft give us a /pet say command!!!!!!! That will have your pet say whatever you type after pet say. Like <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  /pet say But master I don't WANT to attack %t unless you give me a biscut!</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
8.)  Change the Phantom Armor spell to use another reagent besides cats eye. <br>
<br>
We asked for this and phantsmal armor was kind of put into the game. The problem is its super rare off of mobs that are WAY too high for this spells level and it has NO advantage over Phantom armor AND the reagent costs 4p and not the 4s or so that it currently costs. There is no reason to even try to get this spell <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
I suggest changing the cost to something like a bloodstone or maybe jasper. Something thats about 1p a cast. Save us some bag space please <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
9) Mana Regen: Please add a scaling mana regen to our phantom armor line that scales up and boost Transons phantasmal protection to be inline with other classes self mana regen buff.  This works out like this.<br>
<br>
Phantom leather (L 16) +1 mana / tick<br>
Phantom chain  (L 29) +2 mana / tick<br>
Phantom plate  (L 44) +3 mana / tick<br>
Phantom armor  (L 52) +4 mana / tick<br>
Transons phantasmal armor  (L 58.)  +5 mana / tick<br>
<br>
As it stands now Transons is 3 mana per tick and that is 1 pt better the breeze which is a level 16 spell. Clerics for instance, a class with NO form of mana regen gain at L58 a 6 mana per tick spell, Druids gain at 59 a 6 mana per tick spell.<br>
<br>
Enchanters cast breeze at L 16 for 2 mana a tick, clarity at 29 for 7 mana a tick, clarity 2 at 54 for 11 mana a tick and KEI at 60 for 14 mana a tick.<br>
<br>
With these changes it will help a little bit with the large amounts of downtime that magicians deal with and will still be less then ALL the other regen spells out there.<br>
<br>
<br>
10) Add useful summons that people WANT / Need. Stuff that makes them drool for mages to be around. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Here are some suggestions:<br>
<br>
Some proccing weapons starting at 20 damage and moving up to 250 damage  or so (L 20, L 34, L49, L55) <br>
<br>
Some proccing weapons to change a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> pets</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> flavor that are pet only.  25% snare, 30pt dd 5 sec stun, Malosini, lifetap for 55dmg.<br>
<br>
Summon fishing pole (+5% fishing) and 60 bait. Level 12.<br>
<br>
Summon an item with a single Rune Charge on it that absorbs 200 damage or so, make it use a pearl if needed. Rune III costs a jasper and absorbs up to 230 and is level 34. Make this item about L44.<br>
<br>
Lesser Clarity belt: 4 mana / tick +40 hp.<br>
<br>
Make waterstone stack please <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Better summoned armor with some stats for higher end players along with an armor set casters can wear.<br>
<br>
Summone food / water with stats.<br>
<br>
Bandages that actually Heal more per bandage or have a charge of a lesser healing spell or something 50 pts would be good.<br>
<br>
With the ability to put minimum level requirements on items you can easily control the ability to twink some lower level character.<br>
<br>
11) Other thoughts:<br>
<br>
Verant has started to remove the massive amount of downtime ingame with things like binding back at the firepots in TD and the Luclin portals and soon with PoP. So I feel these are not out of line for downtime removers.<br>
<br>
Inter zone CotH<br>
<br>
A port to An Elementalish area. 1 for each element.<br>
<br>
Air: Plane of Air (would use the airstones)<br>
Fire: Lavastorm or Skyfire<br>
Water: Dagnors Cauldron, TD, or Lake Rathetear<br>
Earth: Stonebrunt, Paineel by the Hole or Butcheblock.<br>
<br>
OR perhaps a port to the major libraries across Norrath.<br>
<br>
