<br>
2. Add a spell that makes pets immune to dispel, or just make pets immune to dispel.  Dispelling mobs really reduce a pets power because all buffs (most importantly haste) will be dispelled because pets don't have any instant click items (<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).  Fearing mobs that also dispel are even worse because they will dispel our pet buff that makes pets unfearable, and then our pets will be feared the whole fight.  At the very least, Valiant Companion (pet immune to fear spell) should be made undispellable.<br>
<br>
3. Something needs to be done about pet resists (especially the epic pet which has no extremely strong resist like the normal pets).  Pet only Resist XXXX spells could be added that greatly increase the pets resistance for one element that do not stack with each other (you wouldn’t be able to have resist fire and resist cold on a pet at the same time).  Having pet resists increase with the mages level like I suggested with LVL/ATK would also work.  Having pets die extremely fast from mobs with AE dmg spells, made useless from AE stuns/fears etc, and having the epic pet get slowed every single time from shrooms in FG all sucks a lot.<br>
<br>
4. Frenzied Burnout needs to be fixed.  It should either be an ability that lasts for 6-12 minutes that makes the pet level 60 and does insane damage during that time (huge haste, working flurries, etc) with a 2 hour refresh; this fix would be for an ability on par with mana burn.  Another fix would be to make it increase pets level some, max dmg a little, hp a lil, more haste than Burnout 4 that lasts for 12 minutes with a 12 minute recast time; this fix would be for an ability more on par with dire charm.  Mages need a nice class skill like wizards have with manaburn and enchanters have with dire charm, and frenzied burnout in it's current state is no where near the strength of either of those.<br>
<br>
5. The pet haste cap needs to be removed or raised.  At this moment Burnout 4 and Muzzle of Mardu are pretty useless because Burnout 3 will get you to the cap (at least with the epic pet).  Also, Frenzied Burnout will never work unless the haste cap is removed or raised.<br>
<br>
6. We need a slight nuke upgrade.  A conjure nuke that is slightly better than a druids best nuke (lil more dmg, better ratio, lower cast time, lower resist rate) would be appropriate.  1200 Damage would be great.  It should be as difficult to obtain as the druids moon fire.  It should NOT drop off of emp/seru/VT mobs.  If a mage nuke were to be added that drops off emp/seru/VT mobs, it should do around 1400 Damage.  This would put mages back in the 2nd best nuke category where they should be, druids should not be nuking for more than us.  An easy way to do this would be to upgrade Shock of Fiery Blades (level 60 mage SOL drop spell).<br>
